00:25:19,680 --> 00:25:23,940
♪  for a true lover?  ♪

252
00:25:23,940 --> 00:25:28,180
♪  I'll remember all your love  ♪

253
00:25:28,180 --> 00:25:31,900
♪  till the end of time  ♪

254
00:25:33,980 --> 00:25:36,500
Coming home so late? Did you have supper?

255
00:25:36,500 --> 00:25:38,860
No. Did you cook anything?

256
00:25:38,860 --> 00:25:41,920
I thought you wouldn't eat at home. So I just had some snacks.

257
00:25:41,920 --> 00:25:45,060
I didn't cook. Come on. Have some of these.

258
00:25:45,060 --> 00:25:47,780
Soda crackers that won't gain you weight.

259
00:25:48,500 --> 00:25:52,200
Buy one, get one free at the supermarket. What a steal, huh?

260
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:54,840
This one's yours, and this one's mine.

261
00:25:54,840 --> 00:25:58,260
I hate soda crackers the most. Don't you know that?

262
00:25:59,900 --> 00:26:03,020
What do you have against crackers?

263
00:26:03,020 --> 00:26:05,240
♪  Are you also waiting  ♪

264
00:26:16,580 --> 00:26:21,060
 Right. Why are you mad at the crackers?

265
00:26:21,060 --> 00:26:23,460
 What exactly are you mad at?

266
00:26:23,460 --> 00:26:28,040
 Isn't this nice? The simple boss-employee relationship.

267
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:40,280
Wei'an, why do you look chubbier after being tortured by Gu Yunzheng?

268
00:26:40,280 --> 00:26:42,240
What chubbier?

269
00:26:42,240 --> 00:26:45,200
This is obesity due to overwork.

270
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:48,020
I wonder what Gu Yunzheng's up to.

271
00:26:48,020 --> 00:26:51,725
He keeps feeding me his and his girlfriend's leftovers.

272
00:26:52,900 --> 00:26:54,740
Well, you can choose not to.

273
00:26:54,740 --> 00:26:58,180
Rejecting it won't count as a violation, right?

274
00:26:58,180 --> 00:27:02,460
But the thing is, they don't look like leftovers at all.

275
00:27:02,460 --> 00:27:06,980
Never mind. I'll just eat them as work meals.

276
00:27:11,140 --> 00:27:13,040
It's Dr. Li.

277
00:27:14,580 --> 00:27:17,800
Then could the one beside her be...

278
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:23,240
Bye.

279
00:27:24,060 --> 00:27:25,060
Eliot?

280
00:27:25,060 --> 00:27:26,560

281
00:27:26,560 --> 00:27:28,640
Eliot has come to China?

282
00:27:28,640 --> 00:27:31,540
Why would he be with Li Wantong?

283
00:27:34,080 --> 00:27:38,280
Dr. Gu and Dr. Li's relationship doesn't seem to have gone well, huh?

284
00:27:55,435 --> 00:27:57,780
 Does he know about this or not?

285
00:27:57,780 --> 00:28:00,060
 Should I tell him?

286
00:28:03,820 --> 00:28:05,890

287
00:28:08,040 --> 00:28:09,430

288
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:13,760
 He hasn't sent messages to me for days.

289
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:17,600
Today's operations are all Dr. Gu's?

290
00:28:17,600 --> 00:28:20,740
Yeah, I heard that he asked for that.

291
00:28:20,740 --> 00:28:25,340
And he's been sullen these two days. Seems like someone has offended him.

292
00:28:30,580 --> 00:28:34,360

293
00:28:50,400 --> 00:28:52,400
You scared me.

294
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:55,420
Are you looking for me or my boss? Why didn't you make a sound?

295
00:28:55,420 --> 00:29:01,000
Fang Mingfan, for how focused you were, I'm certain that you'll be an excellent surgeon.

296
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:02,720
Really?

297
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:04,620
I'm here for Dr. Gu.

298
00:29:04,620 --> 00:29:07,680
He's in the operating room. I'm afraid you won't see him today.

299
00:29:07,680 --> 00:29:10,200
Why is he having so many operations lately?

300
00:29:10,200 --> 00:29:11,760
Isn't he always like this?

301
00:29:11,760 --> 00:29:15,640
He said he was busy this week and told me to schedule this operation myself.

302
00:29:15,640 --> 00:29:19,620
But it's already Tuesday, and I haven't figured out the operation approach yet.

303
00:29:21,220 --> 00:29:22,880
Take a look?

304
00:29:23,980 --> 00:29:25,760
The lesion isn't big.

305
00:29:25,760 --> 00:29:30,040
We've done an evaluation. Pick the approach that you're most sure of.

306
00:29:30,040 --> 00:29:33,220
Dr. Fang, considering your mental status,

307
00:29:33,220 --> 00:29:36,560
since it took you two years after failing your first operation to gain the courage again,

308
00:29:36,560 --> 00:29:39,060
you'd better make no mistake this time.

309
00:29:39,060 --> 00:29:42,980
So you can build confidence again and gradually desensitize yourself to that accident.

310
00:29:42,980 --> 00:29:45,660
This is both being responsible to you and your patient.

311
00:29:45,660 --> 00:29:49,460
Although the approach with minimal damage to the patient is quite difficult to operate with,

312
00:29:49,460 --> 00:29:53,420
Dr. Fang has practiced it numerous times. It's already engraved on his mind.

313
00:29:53,420 --> 00:29:57,040
On the operating table, shouldn't doctors be purely focused?

314
00:29:57,040 --> 00:30:01,460
Picking up the scalpel is for doing what's best for the patient.

315
00:30:01,460 --> 00:30:05,380
If you put your personal honor before your patient,

316
00:30:05,380 --> 00:30:08,820
you'll never become a qualified surgeon.

317
00:30:08,820 --> 00:30:11,320
You'd better change your profession.

318
00:30:11,320 --> 00:30:14,980
Give patients the best treatment.

319
00:30:16,500 --> 00:30:18,880
It's the same as my boss said.

320
00:30:19,980 --> 00:30:22,040
I see.

321
00:30:22,680 --> 00:30:24,880
Thank you, Su Wei'an.

322
00:30:31,140 --> 00:30:32,980
Su Wei'an,

323
00:30:36,340 --> 00:30:38,340
you seem to have a problem with me.

324
00:30:38,340 --> 00:30:39,260
No.

325
00:30:39,260 --> 00:30:41,880
I'm a psychologist. That's the least I can tell.

326
00:30:41,880 --> 00:30:43,980
You're overthinking.

327
00:30:49,140 --> 00:30:54,040
Well, Dr. Li. Dr. Gu is a good man.

328
00:30:55,040 --> 00:30:59,060
Even if you want to friend zone Gu Yunzheng, you shouldn't do this to me, right?

329
00:30:59,060 --> 00:31:00,580
Of course, I know he's a good man.

330
00:31:00,580 --> 00:31:03,640
Otherwise, previously, I wouldn't have chased him so hard.

331
00:31:03,640 --> 00:31:08,480
Since you've made him your boyfriend, I hope that you will cherish him.

332
00:31:08,480 --> 00:31:14,130
Adults should be responsible for their own actions. Do not hurt people's feelings.

333
00:31:16,580 --> 00:31:21,020
Wait, what? I've made Gu Yunzheng my boyfriend?

334
00:31:21,020 --> 00:31:23,480
Why didn't I know such a good thing?

335
00:31:31,160 --> 00:31:33,540
Su Wei'an.

336
00:31:33,540 --> 00:31:34,860
What now?

337
00:31:34,860 --> 00:31:36,100
I'm telling you, Su Wei'an.

338
00:31:36,100 --> 00:31:39,860
My dad spent more than a decade developing that drug. There can't be anything wrong.

339
00:31:39,860 --> 00:31:43,040
Your aunt's aneurysm is purely bad luck.

340
00:31:43,040 --> 00:31:46,580
It has nothing to do with HDQ39.

341
00:31:48,980 --> 00:31:51,700
You secretly read my aunt's Adverse Event Report?

342
00:31:51,700 --> 00:31:55,840
Didn't you mail it to my home especially for me to read?

343
00:31:55,840 --> 00:31:58,260
You even used a Jiehui express envelope.

344
00:31:58,260 --> 00:31:59,480
What?

345
00:31:59,480 --> 00:32:03,840
Are you trying to declare that Du Yuncheng is yours?

346
00:32:05,140 --> 00:32:09,460
Except for members of the research team, no one's authorized to read that report. Don't you know that?

347
00:32:09,460 --> 00:32:13,980
Not only did I read it, I also tore it up.

348
00:32:17,320 --> 00:32:19,900
What can you do with me?

349
00:32:22,200 --> 00:32:25,780
Wen Ran, you're a medical student, too.

350
00:32:25,780 --> 00:32:28,000
Don't you know that during the drug trial,

351
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:33,260
any adverse event must be reported to the development team as soon as it's discovered?

352
00:32:33,260 --> 00:32:34,440
This is the formal procedure.

353
00:32:34,440 --> 00:32:36,360
Stop giving me the procedure talk.

354
00:32:36,360 --> 00:32:40,080
I'm telling you, Su Wei'an. You're also a carrier of the HD gene.

355
00:32:40,080 --> 00:32:43,640
HDQ39 is the most promising specific drug to go on the market.

356
00:32:43,640 --> 00:32:47,960
If you ever dare to ruin it, you'll be ruining yourself, too.

357
00:32:54,700 --> 00:32:56,620
I'm sorry, Wei'an.

358
00:32:56,620 --> 00:32:58,380
I did it in too much of a hurry.

359
00:32:58,380 --> 00:33:03,660
I didn't expect that it was opened by Wen Ran after being delivered to Professor Wen's home.

360
00:33:03,660 --> 00:33:09,060
I'm thinking, is it possible that Professor Wen didn't even know about this?

361
00:33:09,060 --> 00:33:10,740
It's possible.

362
00:33:10,740 --> 00:33:13,700
Then I'll send another copy to Zhang He Hospital.

363
00:33:13,700 --> 00:33:16,500
No need. I'll go there personally.

364
00:33:16,500 --> 00:33:20,580
I'll deliver it to Professor Wen. This is safer.

365
00:33:21,660 --> 00:33:22,740
Good.

366
00:33:22,740 --> 00:33:29,080

367
00:33:34,920 --> 00:33:39,380
Director Yang, do you still remember me?

368
00:33:39,380 --> 00:33:43,740
- Can I help you? 
 - I'd like to meet Prof. Wen. Where's his office, please?

369
00:33:43,740 --> 00:33:46,700
Professor Wen is out for a meeting. You can tell me if there's anything.

370
00:33:46,700 --> 00:33:48,460
Here's the thing.

371
00:33:48,460 --> 00:33:52,980
In Phase III of the HDQ39 clinical trial, there's a subject called Su Yuan.

372
00:33:52,980 --> 00:33:54,680
Does it ring a bell?

373
00:33:54,680 --> 00:33:56,360
Yes, I think so. What is it?

374
00:33:56,360 --> 00:34:00,120
After the drug test, she had two aneurysm ruptures.

375
00:34:00,120 --> 00:34:03,760
I'm not sure if they're caused by HDQ39.

376
00:34:06,240 --> 00:34:09,580
This is an Adverse Event Report prepared by me. Her medical record is also in it.

377
00:34:09,580 --> 00:34:13,460
If it's not too much trouble, please give it to Professor Wen for me.

378
00:34:19,340 --> 00:34:22,300
Okay. I'll give it to him as soon as possible.

379
00:34:22,300 --> 00:34:24,250
Thank you.

380
00:34:24,720 --> 00:34:28,480
If it's convenient, could you give me his contact information?

381
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:30,360
I'd like to tell him personally.

382
00:34:30,360 --> 00:34:34,520
Professor Wen is a busy man. You can send emails to our public mailbox on our website.

383
00:34:34,520 --> 00:34:36,860
I check the inbox every day.

384
00:34:36,860 --> 00:34:39,500
Okay, thank you.

385
00:35:08,500 --> 00:35:12,820

386
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:18,740

387
00:35:23,880 --> 00:35:29,340

388
00:35:29,340 --> 00:35:30,540

389
00:35:37,280 --> 00:35:39,040
- This won't do. 
 - Okay.

390
00:35:39,040 --> 00:35:42,280
Su Wei'an, why are you here so late?

391
00:35:42,280 --> 00:35:43,920
Are you feeling unwell?

392
00:35:43,920 --> 00:35:47,660
No. I was handling some personal things.

393
00:35:48,180 --> 00:35:50,280
Handling personal things during work hours?

394
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:53,160
This is absenteeism.

395
00:35:54,800 --> 00:35:56,820
Look at the time now.

396
00:35:58,600 --> 00:36:01,140
The files I delivered to Professor Wen were blocked by Wen Ran.

397
00:36:01,140 --> 00:36:05,160
I went to Zhang He Hospital this morning to resubmit them.

398
00:36:06,720 --> 00:36:10,680
Go ahead if you want to deduct my pay. It's your lab after all.

399
00:36:15,360 --> 00:36:17,480
You could've just explained it.

400
00:36:17,480 --> 00:36:20,580
It's not like I'll do it every time.

401
00:36:23,800 --> 00:36:28,500
You know what. Zhang He Hospital is known for its low efficiency.

402
00:36:28,500 --> 00:36:33,640
I sent an email to their public mailbox last weekend. But there's no reply even now.

403
00:36:34,800 --> 00:36:37,280
That's odd.

404
00:36:37,280 --> 00:36:40,180
Director Yang told me that he would check the inbox every day.

405
00:36:40,180 --> 00:36:42,380
Who's Director Yang?

406
00:36:45,380 --> 00:36:49,900
Su Wei'an, if there's really a problem, just tell me.

407
00:36:49,900 --> 00:36:51,260
I can help you solve it together.

408
00:36:51,260 --> 00:36:54,320
No need. I can handle it myself.

409
00:36:54,320 --> 00:36:59,620
By the way, how many more files to translate? Can you give them to me in one go?

410
00:36:59,620 --> 00:37:04,340
I still need to take care of my aunt. I don't have that much time to keep working for you.

411
00:37:04,340 --> 00:37:08,420
Still a lot to come. I'll tell you when I sort them out.

412
00:37:14,520 --> 00:37:16,420
Yuncheng?

413
00:37:19,780 --> 00:37:21,845
Yuncheng?

414
00:37:21,845 --> 00:37:23,900
Are you here to pick me up?

415
00:37:23,900 --> 00:37:25,660
Get in.

416
00:37:40,780 --> 00:37:43,043
It's windy at night.

417
00:37:43,043 --> 00:37:44,943
I'm so cold.

418
00:37:45,770 --> 00:37:48,410
Did you take Su Wei'an's report?

419
00:37:50,160 --> 00:37:52,520
You met me because of Su Wei'an again?

420
00:37:52,520 --> 00:37:55,060
Just answer me yes or no.

421
00:37:55,060 --> 00:37:56,460
Yes.

422
00:37:56,460 --> 00:38:00,400
The Adverse Event Report she mailed was torn up by me.

423
00:38:00,400 --> 00:38:03,400
What? She specially went to Jiehui to mail it?

424
00:38:03,400 --> 00:38:06,000
Or did you invite her to a certain exhibition?

425
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:09,980
I'm warning you. Stay away from Su Wei'an.

426
00:38:09,980 --> 00:38:13,220
Even if she's going to ruin your project,

427
00:38:13,220 --> 00:38:15,400
you're still trying to defend her?

428
00:38:15,400 --> 00:38:18,660
That's between me and her. It has nothing to do with you.

429
00:38:18,660 --> 00:38:22,400
And, do not come to Jiehui anymore.

430
00:38:22,400 --> 00:38:24,160
We've broken up.

431
00:38:24,160 --> 00:38:28,680
Don't pretend that you're still my girlfriend in front of my employees.

432
00:38:28,680 --> 00:38:32,280
If I run into that, don't blame me for being rude.

433
00:38:32,280 --> 00:38:36,280
I'm busy now. I can't drive you home.

434
00:38:36,280 --> 00:38:38,300
Yuncheng.

435
00:38:38,300 --> 00:38:40,300
Yuncheng!

436
00:38:55,680 --> 00:38:57,360
You're home.

437
00:39:07,400 --> 00:39:08,900
What happened?

438
00:39:08,900 --> 00:39:11,880
Did anyone bully my baby girl?

439
00:39:16,920 --> 00:39:18,880
What happened, Xiao Ran?

440
00:39:20,300 --> 00:39:24,940
Dad, am I a fool?

441
00:39:24,940 --> 00:39:27,820
Do I trust people too easily?

442
00:39:27,820 --> 00:39:29,920
What exactly is going on?

443
00:39:29,920 --> 00:39:32,080
Tell me.

444
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:37,800
Do you still remember my paper was wrongly accused, and my name was withdrawn from it?

445
00:39:38,620 --> 00:39:44,260
That classmate was called Su Wei'an. She was later expelled.

446
00:39:44,260 --> 00:39:46,800
A while ago, she approached me

447
00:39:46,800 --> 00:39:51,590
and asked me to help her aunt take part in the HDQ39 clinical trial.

448
00:39:52,160 --> 00:39:56,440
Haven't I told you already? That is a serious matter.

449
00:39:56,440 --> 00:39:59,820
The admission is all random. You can't interfere.

450
00:39:59,820 --> 00:40:04,400
Yeah. That's what I told her.

451
00:40:04,400 --> 00:40:06,900
But I don't know what has got into her.

452
00:40:06,900 --> 00:40:10,760
She has spread rumors that HDQ39 has side effects.

453
00:40:10,760 --> 00:40:13,820
I think she's trying to get back at me.

454
00:40:13,820 --> 00:40:17,400
Xiao Ran, what exactly did she say?

455
00:40:17,400 --> 00:40:21,958
If there's truly an adverse event, I want to talk to her in person.

456
00:40:21,958 --> 00:40:24,280
No need, Dad.

457
00:40:24,280 --> 00:40:28,580
She's just dark-minded. She just hates to see me happy.

458
00:40:28,580 --> 00:40:30,000
You know what?

459
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:33,370
Back at school, she had a crush on Yuncheng.

460
00:40:33,370 --> 00:40:38,990
Now she knows that I'm his girlfriend, she becomes jealous of me.

461
00:40:38,990 --> 00:40:41,060
Lately, she keeps badgering Yuncheng.

462
00:40:41,060 --> 00:40:44,560
Yuncheng ignores her, but she just won't give up.

463
00:40:44,560 --> 00:40:46,540
She just has to break us up.

464
00:40:46,540 --> 00:40:50,160
How can this girl be so shameless?

465
00:40:50,880 --> 00:40:52,880
Yeah.

466
00:40:54,280 --> 00:40:59,580
Dad, if she ever comes to bother you, you mustn't talk to her.

467
00:40:59,580 --> 00:41:00,680
I see.

468
00:41:00,680 --> 00:41:04,300
All right, stop being upset now.

469
00:41:04,300 --> 00:41:07,080
Go take a shower and go to bed.

470
00:41:16,580 --> 00:41:19,240
Su Wei'an.

471
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:31,280
Hi, Eliot.

472
00:41:31,280 --> 00:41:37,260
 Gu, the literature and files you asked me to look for, I've told my assistant to send them to your mailbox.

473
00:41:37,260 --> 00:41:39,800
That's great, Eliot. Thank you.

474
00:41:39,800 --> 00:41:42,160
You did me a great favor this time.

475
00:41:42,160 --> 00:41:46,840
What you told me to look for are the most cutting-edge gene editing technologies.

476
00:41:46,840 --> 00:41:49,520
Will this help your research on gliomas?

477
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:51,540
I have my reasons.

478
00:41:51,540 --> 00:41:55,220
How about this? I'll treat you to dinner before you go back home.

479
00:41:55,220 --> 00:41:56,860
Bye.

480
00:42:03,090 --> 00:42:07,240

481
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:13,680

482
00:42:18,420 --> 00:42:21,640
These are the remaining files to be translated.

483
00:42:21,640 --> 00:42:25,400
When you finish them, your work is done.

484
00:42:33,880 --> 00:42:37,000
Where did you get so much French literature?

485
00:42:37,000 --> 00:42:40,080
Take your time. I'm in no hurry.

486
00:42:40,080 --> 00:42:44,440
Be careful when you're translating. You'll have to redo it if you mistranslate any.

487
00:42:44,440 --> 00:42:46,280
That'll be a huge waste of time.

488
00:42:46,280 --> 00:42:49,620
No worries. I'll definitely complete the mission with due quality and quantity.

489
00:42:49,620 --> 00:42:52,260
No redoing.

490
00:42:57,540 --> 00:42:59,520
This is too much.

